                    <div class="chartbeat">       
                        <div class="job">

                        <h3>Senior Product Manager</h3>

                    	<h4>May 2014 - Present</h4>

                    <p>Building products that help journalists and online publishers measure
                        and act upon audience attention data.</p>
                    <ul>
                    <p style="font-style:italic">More recently...</p>
                      <li>Managed the roadmap for Chartbeat's flagship SaaS product, a mature editorial analytics platform used by 80% of the top publishers in the US and ~50,000 media sites in over 60 countries around the world.</li>
                      <li>Managed the day-to-day product development process for Chartbeat's two core product teams.</li>
                      <li>Set Chartbeat's product strategy in partnership with the VP of Product and Engineering.</li>
                      <li>Revamped Chartbeat's internal product analytics to help facilitate more data-driven product decisions.</li>
                      <li>Built Chartbeat's process for the intake and management of customer feature requests and bug reports.</li>
                      <li>Represented the product team in sales initiatives for top-tier and strategic prospects.</li>
                      <li>Conducted stakeholder and user research in partnership with the design team.</li> 
                      
                    <p style="font-style:italic">Less recently...</p>
                        <li>Led a small team of software engineers, designers, and data scientists to rapidly research, and develop prototypes for new products.</li>
                        <li>Conceptualized and developed a real-time clustering algorithm for news article topic classification in partnership with Chartbeat's data science research team.</li>
                        <li>Managed the roadmap for Chartbeat&#39;s time-based display advertising
                            product and helped design and launch the world&#39;s first cost-per-hour
                            campaigns with the Financial Times and The Economist.</li>
                        <li>Worked with internal teams and external auditors to attain Media Ratings
                            Council accredidation for Chartbeat&#39;s advertising metrics.</li>
                        <li>Managed relationships with various advertising technology companies to
                            strategize and build partner integrations.</li>
                    </ul>
